Traditional Scholarly Page Layout — Rules (3-Commentary Edition)
Overview
This layout system renders a main text with three parallel commentary systems, where all four content layers are typeset together on a single page. The page is fully calculated: the main text and all its associated notes from the three systems always appear together without overflow to the next page.

Page Structure (Top to Bottom)
Page Number: Positioned top-left (or top-right on verso pages). Small and muted.

Running Header: A single line spanning full width. Contains metadata (book, section, position) separated by delimiters like · or |.

Main Text Block: Divided into two equal columns. Full vocalization (nikud). Contains three types of inline reference markers (A, B, and C).

Commentary System 1: - Header: Centered, bold title.

Body: 2 columns, justified, continuous text flow (no line breaks between notes).

Commentary System 2:

Header: Centered, bold title below System 1 body.

Body: 2 columns, justified, continuous text flow.

Commentary System 3:

Header: Centered, bold title below System 2 body.

Body: 2 columns, justified, continuous text flow.

Typography & Styling Specifications
Running Header: Size: 10–11px | Weight: Regular | Alignment: Left or spread.

Main Text Block: Size: 14–16px | Weight: Regular | Vocalization: Full (Nikud) | Layout: 2 columns, Justified.

Commentary Headers (1, 2, & 3): Size: 13px | Weight: Bold | Alignment: Centered.

Commentary Bodies (1, 2, & 3): Size: 11–12px | Weight: Regular | Vocalization: Partial/None | Layout: 2 columns, Justified.

Gutter / Column Gap: 1em consistent across all blocks.

Direction: Strict RTL (Right-to-Left) for all elements.

Page Calculation — Critical Constraint
The engine must treat the page as a single calculation unit:

Identify main-text lines and their corresponding notes for all 3 systems.

Greedy Fit Algorithm: If the total height of (Main Text + System 1 + System 2 + System 3) exceeds page height, reduce Main Text lines one by one until all associated notes fit on the current page.

No Overflow: Notes must never move to the next page without their corresponding main text anchor.

Reference Marker System
System 1 Markers: Hebrew letters (א, ב, ג).

System 2 Markers: Numerals (1, 2, 3).

System 3 Markers: Symbols (*, †, ‡) or distinct font style.

In-Text: Superscript, reduced size.

In-Commentary: Inline at start of note, bolded, serves as the only separator between notes.

Implementation Guidelines for AI
CSS Layout: Use column-count: 2 for multi-column blocks. Do not use flex/float for text columns.

RTL Support: Set direction: rtl on the root container.

Zero Whitespace: Commentary notes must have no margins, padding, or display: block between them. They must flow like a single paragraph.

Bidirectional Links: Use unique IDs (ref-a1, note-a1, etc.) to ensure markers and notes are correctly paired during the layout calculation.